</header><!-- header -->	<div class="financity-page-wrapper" id="financity-page-wrapper" ><div class="gdlr-core-page-builder-body"><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper  hero-section" style="padding: 150px 0px 150px 0px;" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-background-wrap"  ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-background gdlr-core-parallax gdlr-core-js" style="background-image: url(http://125.63.74.98:6324/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_257347054-4.jpg) ;background-size: cover ;background-position: center ;"  data-parallax-speed="0.8"  ></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper-content gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper-container clearfix gdlr-core-container" ><div class=" gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper-container-inner clearfix"  ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 80px ;text-transform: uppercase ;color: #ffffff ;"  ><p style="text-align: center;">LIFE INSURANCE</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-wrapper " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 41px;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-container gdlr-core-line-height-0 clearfix gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-container"><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-content  gdlr-core-column-45 gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-padding gdlr-core-line-height gdlr-core-column-extend-right"  ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-content-inner"  ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 22px ;text-transform: none ;color: #000000 ;"  ><p style="text-align: left;"><strong>It wasn&#8217;t until 1732, that the first insurance company in the United </strong><strong>States formed in Charlestone, S.C., and life insurance wasn&#8217;t added to </strong><strong>its product line until 1760. A lot has changed since then.</strong></p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js " style="margin: 40px 0px 0px 0px;"   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap "  ><h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 22px ;text-transform: none ;"  >Term Life Insurance<span class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-divider gdlr-core-skin-divider" ></span></h3></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align text-box-para"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 16px ;text-transform: none ;color: #141414 ;"  ><p>Term Life Insurance is straight-forward and affordable life insurance product, which offers temporary coverage. You will be covered for specific term and the premiums will be guaranteed for that period of time. Term plans range from 10 to 40 years, followed with the option to renew. This type of insurance is the least expensive way to acquire a significant death benefit. You also have the option to convert to Permanent Insurance, prior to age of 71, without additional medical exams or questionnaires.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb  gdlr-core-accordion-style-box-icon gdlr-core-allow-close-all own-accordian accordion-heading"  ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix  gdlr-core-active" ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-border"></div><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper"><h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js ">TERM INSURANCE CAN :</h4><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content"><p>&#8211; Protect your income<br />
&#8211; Protect a mortgage or business loan<br />
&#8211; Fund buy-sell agreements<br />
&#8211; Pay for your children&#8217;s education<br />
&#8211; Cover your final expenses</p>
</div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix " ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-border"></div><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper"><h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js ">MORTGAGE INSURANCE FACTS :</h4><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content"><p>&#8211; The death benefits decreases with the mortgage.<br />
&#8211; Eligibility is considered at the time of claim.<br />
&#8211; Can be renewed every 5 years.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap "  ><h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 21px ;font-weight: bold ;"  >PERMANENT INSURANCE<span class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-divider gdlr-core-skin-divider" ></span></h3></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap "  ><h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight: 500 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;"  >T-100 INSURANCE<span class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-divider gdlr-core-skin-divider" ></span></h3></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align text-box-para" style="padding-bottom: 8px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 16px ;text-transform: none ;"  ><p>Term 100 is a permanent insurance product that has fixed premiums until the insured turns 100 years of age.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap "  ><h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight: 500 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;"  >WHOLE LIFE INSURANCE<span class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-divider gdlr-core-skin-divider" ></span></h3></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align text-box-para" style="padding-bottom: 8px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 16px ;text-transform: none ;"  ><p>Whole Life is a life insurance policy guaranteed to remain in force for the person&#8217;s lifetime. This insurance product builds a guaranteed cash value; a saving accumulation which can be borrowed against or withdrawn tax free. You also have the opinion to pay premiums for a limited number of years 10, 15, 20 or to the age of 65.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap "  ><h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight: 500 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;"  >UNIVERSAL LIFE INSURANCE<span class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-divider gdlr-core-skin-divider" ></span></h3></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align text-box-para" style="padding-bottom: 25px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 16px ;text-transform: none ;"  ><p>Universal Life Insurance is a permanent insurance product combined with investment options, as well as death benefits options, riders, flexible premium options and additional benefits and features tailored to your needs. The investment options in a Universal Life plan can be utilised in many ways and are customised to your financial needs and risk tolerance.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr text-box-headings" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;"  ><div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap "  ><h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 24px ;"  >GUARANTEED & SIMPLIFIED ISSUE<span class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-divider gdlr-core-skin-divider" ></span></h3></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align text-box-para"  ><div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="text-transform: none ;"  ><p>Guaranteed Issue Life Insurance covers those who currently have medical issues or have had medical issues in the past and cannot qualify for standard life insurance or would be rated in a higher price bracket. By answering a few medical questions, you can qualify for up to $500,000 in coverage with no medical exam. In the event of an accidental death, your beneficiary could receive up to five times the basic coverage.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first" ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js "   ><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element" ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb  gdlr-core-accordion-style-box-icon gdlr-core-allow-close-all own-accordian accordion-heading"  ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix  gdlr-core-active" ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-border"></div><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper"><h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js ">GUARANTEED ISSUE ADVANTAGES :</h4><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content"><p>&#8211; Approval for those who cannot qualify for traditional insurance due to history.<br />
&#8211; Approval for those who may be rated.<br />
&#8211; Approval for those who have a hazardous  job or lifestyle.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix " ><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-border"></div><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper"><h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js ">FINAL EXPENSE ADVANTAGES :</h4><div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content"><p>&#8211; Final Expense Insurance covers up to $25,000 in death benefit to alleviate the burden of  having to pay for funeral costs.<br />
&#8211; Option for those who don&#8217;t want any medical exams or health questionnaires.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-left gdlr-core-column-extend-left  financity-sidebar-area gdlr-core-column-15 gdlr-core-pbf-sidebar-padding  gdlr-core-line-height"  ><div class="gdlr-core-sidebar-item"><div id="custom_html-6" class="widget_text widget widget_custom_html financity-widget"><div class="textwidget custom-html-widget"><div class="title-heading">
